    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.52-53_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">52</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Skip and I have been thinking and talking so much of you and Mona since his return from a few days in Oklahoma, where he was lecturing when Mona passed over into the other Life.</p>
                
                <p>I felt you were surrounded by people and very busy, so we postponed our visiting you. But after reading Helen Keller's '<del>m</del><add>M</add>y Religion' last night, it seems sort of natural that there would be a timeless-ness already about our friendship.</p>
                
                <p>Dr. Huston Smith was on the Stephens Campus not long ago and expressed joy again a<del>y</del><add>t</add> making yours and Monas<sic>Mona's</sic> acquaintance at our house about two years ago. He would have liked to visit with you ag<del>i</del><add>a</add>in. He had just spent some time in the far east and several weeks in a Zen-ist monastery and is quite a searcher. Too bad he is going from St. Louis to <hi rend="caps">M.I.T.</hi> and will really be too far away for us to get you two interesting people together again. But we all have more time than we sometimes realize to get togeth<del/><add>e</add>r and talk, or commune or what?</p>
                
                <p>Remember us to Mona when you commune with her.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Most Sincerely, your friends</salute>
                    
                    <signed><unclear>Elly Ellzey</unclear></signed>
                    <signed>the Ellzey's</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.52-53_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">53</fw>
                
                <fw type="postmark">
                    COLUMBIA. MO.
                    APR 24
                    5-PM
                    1958
                
                    PRAY
                    FOR
                    PEACE
                </fw>
